  "texts": [
    "In this way, we endow HistoGPT with existing visual and linguistic domain knowledge, which is critical for generating histopathology reports from entire and serial WSIs.",
    "Following Flamingo 27, we freeze the parameters of all pre-trained modules during optimization to reduce computational cost and avoid catastrophic forgetting of previously acquired knowledge (Supplementary Fig. 1).",
    "In addition, our large model uses a three-dimensional factorized position embedding function 28 to encode the x-and y-coordinates of each patch, as well as the z-coordinate indicating which slide it belongs to.",
    "A language model predicts a probability distribution over a vocabulary: The next word in a text is selected probabilistically based on a combination of temperature, top-p, and top-k sampling.",
    "For HistoGPT, this means that once the first few words have been chosen, the outline of the report is roughly predetermined."
  ],
